```{r}
spotify <- read_csv("data/dataset.csv", show_col_types = FALSE)
```

# Data Preparation

First, I removed rows with missing values in the variables used for the visualization.

```{r}
spotify_clean <- spotify %>%
  drop_na(danceability, energy, popularity, track_name, artists, track_genre)
```

Next, I limited the display to the 10 genres with the most songs so the chart would remain readable and responsive.

```{r}
top_genres <- spotify_clean %>%
  count(track_genre, sort = TRUE) %>%
  slice_head(n = 10) %>%
  pull(track_genre)

spotify_top <- spotify_clean %>%
  filter(track_genre %in% top_genres) %>%
  slice_sample(n = 5000)
```

Summary

```{r}
spotify_top %>%
  summarize(
    tracks = n(),
    genres = n_distinct(track_genre),
    avg_popularity = round(mean(popularity), 2),
    avg_energy = round(mean(energy), 2),
    avg_danceability = round(mean(danceability), 2)
  )
```

# Interactive Visualization

Hover over points to see song details. Click legend items to filter genres.

```{r}
fig <- plot_ly(
  data = spotify_top,
  x = ~energy,
  y = ~danceability,
  color = ~track_genre,
  size = ~popularity,
  sizes = c(8, 20),
  type = "scatter",
  mode = "markers",
  text = ~paste(
    "<b>Track:</b>", track_name,
    "<br><b>Artist:</b>", artists,
    "<br><b>Genre:</b>", track_genre,
    "<br><b>Popularity:</b>", popularity
  ),
  hoverinfo = "text",
  marker = list(opacity = 0.7)
) %>%
  layout(
    title = "Energy vs Danceability by Genre",
    xaxis = list(title = "Energy"),
    yaxis = list(title = "Danceability")
  )

fig
```

# What This Shows

Some genres cluster closely, meaning songs in those genres have similar characteristics. Other genres are more spread out, showing more variety. Popular songs appear in many different areas, which suggests there is no single formula for a hit.

# Explore

Try interacting with the chart:

-    Hover over songs

-    Turn genres on/off in the legend

-    Look for clusters or patterns

# Conclusion

This visualization shows that songs differ widely across genres, and popularity is not limited to one specific combination of energy and danceability. The interactive chart makes it easier to explore these patterns and compare songs directly.
